<br>
Sure some people made it worth your while and gave you something decent like 25 plat - 100 plat.  But most of the time, people would give you crap or stiff you.<br>
<br>
So do I cast it anymore in nexus?  No, it's not worth my time.  I can camp somewhere get exp and earn more cash or items instead.<br>
<br>
Now I have to go /role or /anon cause all these people ask for a buff whenever I'm not, especially when in PoTranq, or in PoK.  I've even had people get pissed at me for saying no.  One time some idiot got pissed because I said no oom, just rezzed, can you believe that?<br>
<br>
So my stone hard policy now is...nobody gets that buff unless they are a good friend or in my guild.  That's it.  People still ask even when I'm busy or /role or /anon ...tough.  No enchanters left casting in nexus...too bad.   If the guy who started this thread wants to sit in Nexus for hours and cast a buff for free...go ahead...please.  If someone like him on my server did this 24/7, that would keep the damn crack beggars off my back.<br>
<br>
Note to any non-enchanters reading this: if an enchanter is /anon or /roleplay don't ask for a fricken crack buff.  And if he says no leave him the f alone ok?  It's not his duty to buff you.  Thanks.<br>
